The paper deals with a logical formalism for reasoning about programs with both angelic and demonic nondeterminism, which is a topic in logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of the formalism for synthesis of implementations, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on formal methods and logical calculi suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) and game theory (cs.GT).
